False alarm
-----------
A false alarm from Bali, where the realities of the rabies outbreak that started in 2008 have been quite bad enough, may already have circulated far and wide. I'm trying to overtake it.

The 13 Jan 2012 edition of the 'Bali Times' inexplicably includes an article headlined "New Death Sparks Renewed Rabies Fear." (http://www.thebalitimes.com/2012/01/16/new-death-sparks-renewed-rabies-fear/). The article begins: "Officials fear that rabies may have reached Nusa Penida, one of the few parts of Bali to remain free of the disease, after a local woman died of the disease last week. Head of rabies management at Sanglah Hospital Dr Ken Warasandhi said that 2 patients from Klungkung regency had died of suspected rabies last week. He identified them as 43 year old and 58 year old patients.

This article appears to be a paraphrasing or translation of an article which originally appeared in the local language newspaper 'Radar Bali' on 8 Jan 2011 -- just over one year ago.

--
